definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  4-nitrocatechol + O2 + 4 e- + 3 H+ -eq- H2O + nitrite + 1,2,4-benzenetriol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-chlorophenoxyacetate + 1|2 O2 -eq- glyoxylate + 4-chlorophenol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tert-butanol + 1|2 O2 -eq- 2-methyl-2-hydroxy-1-propanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-pinene + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- H2O + pinocarveol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dimethylsilanediol + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- H2O + hydroxymethylmethylsilanediol.
Catalysis of the oxidation of alkanes (up to C8) to alcohols and alkenes (up to C5) to epoxides and alcohols in the presence of ammonium ions.
Catalysis of the reaction -  hydroxymethylsilanetriol + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- 2 H2O + formylsilanetriol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxyisobutyrate + 1|2 O2 -eq- 2,3-dihydroxy-2-methyl propionate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-pinene + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- H2O + myrtenol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-nitrophenol + H(+) + NADH + O(2) -eq- 4-nitrocatechol + H(2)O + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetate + 2-oxoglutarate + oxygen -eq- 2,4-dichlorophenol + glyoxylate + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nitrobenzene + NADH + O2 -eq- NAD+ + nitrite + catechol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-aminobenzoate + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 e- -eq- NH3 + 3,4-dihydroxybenzoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  toluene-4-sulfonate + NADH + O2 + H+ -eq- NAD+ + HSO3(-) + 4-methylcatechol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-indanone + NADPH + 1|2 O2 -eq- NADP+ + 3,4-dihydrocoumarin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-indanone + NADPH + 1|2 O2 -eq- NADP+ + 3-hydroxy-1-indanone.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-unsubstituted benzenoid + O2 + NAD(P)H + H+ -eq- 2,3-cis-dihydroxydihydrobenzenoid + NAD(P)+. Substrates include 1,4-dichlorobenzene (forms 3,6-dichloro-cis-1,2-dihydroxycyclohexa-3,5-diene), 1,2,3,4-tetrachlorobenzene (forms cis-chlorobenzene dihydrodiol) and 1,2,4-trichlorobenzene (forms 3,4,6-trichloro-cis-1,2-dihydroxycyclohexa-3,5-diene).
Catalysis of the reaction -  dibenzofuran + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- 2,2',3-trihydroxybiphenyl + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  methylbenzoate + NADH + O2 + H+ -eq- NAD+ + 1,2-dihydroxymethylcyclohexa-3,5-dienecarboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dibenzothiophene + NADH + O2 + H+ -eq- NAD+ + cis-1,2-dihydroxy-1,2-dihydrodibenzothiophene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9-fluorenone + 2 NADPH + O2 -eq- 2 NADP+ + 3,4-dihydroxy-3,4-dihydro-9-fluorenone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ethylbenzene + O2 + NADH + H+ -eq- NAD+ + cis-2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dihydroethylbenzene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-indanone + NADPH + 1|2 O2 -eq- NADP+ + 3-isochromanone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3,5-trihydroxytoluene + O2 -eq- 2,4,6-trioxoheptanoate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  anthranilate + NADPH + H+ + O2 -eq- catechol + CO2 + NADP+ + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzene + H(+) + NADH + O(2) -eq- cis-cyclohexa-3,5-diene-1,2-diol + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + NADH + O(2) + phthalate -eq- cis-4,5-dihydroxycyclohexa-2,6-diene-1,2-dicarboxylate + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-sulfobenzoate + H(+) + NADH + O(2) -eq- 3,4-dihydroxybenzoate + NAD(+) + sulfite.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-chlorophenylacetate + NADH + O(2) -eq- 3,4-dihydroxyphenylacetate + chloride + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoate + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- catechol + CO2 + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + NADH + O(2) + toluene -eq- (1S,2R)-3-methylcyclohexa-3,5-diene-1,2-diol + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  naphthalene + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- (1R,2S)-1,2-dihydronaphthalene-1,2-diol + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-chlorobenzoate + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- catechol + chloride + NAD+ + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-aminobenzenesulfonate + 2 H(+) + NADH + O(2) -eq- 2,3-dihydroxybenzenesulfonate + NAD(+) + NH(4)(+). 2,3-dihydroxybenzenesulfonate is also known as 3-sulfocatechol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + NADH + O(2) + terephthalate -eq- (3S,4R)-3,4-dihydroxycyclohexa-1,5-diene-1,4-dicarboxylate + NAD(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  quinolin-2-ol + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- 2,5,6-trihydroxy-5,6-dihydroquinoline + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxytoluene + NADH + O2 -eq- NAD+ + OH- + 3-hydroxybenzyl alcohol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenylacetate + NADH + O2 -eq- NAD+ + OH- + 2-hydroxyphenylacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  p-nitrophenol + O2 + NADPH -eq- H2O + NADP+ + nitrite + p-benzoquinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dimethyl sulfide + NADH + O2 -eq- NAD+ + OH- + methanethiol + formaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-pinene + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- NAD+ + H2O + alpha-pinene oxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (4R)-limonene + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 -eq- NAD(P)+ + H2O + (4R)-limonene-1,2-epoxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenanthrene + O2 + NADH + H+ -eq- H2O + NAD+ + phenanthrene-9,10-oxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-hydroxy-2-naphthoate + O2 + NADPH + 2 H+ -eq- NADP+ + H2O + CO2 + 1,2-dihydroxynaphthalene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  toluene + 1|2 O2 -eq- 4-hydroxytoluene.
Catalysis of the reactions -  toluene + 1|2 O2 -eq- benzyl alcohol, and xylene + 1|2 O2 -eq- methylbenzyl alcohol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dibenzothiophene + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- dibenzothiophene-5-oxide + NAD+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-hydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- H2O + 5,6-dihydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline.
